msgctxt "116_Annoyed Man"
msgid "How can this not be good enough? The texture of the noodles, the flavor of the soup... It's all exactly the same as Kyushu No. 1 Star ramen!"
msgstr "¡¿Cómo es posible que esto no sea suficiente?! El sabor de la sopa... ¡Es exactamente igual al ramen de Kyushu No. 1 Star!"

msgctxt "128_Man in Suit"
msgid "True... There's no question that it's faithful to Kyushu No. 1 Star ramen."
msgstr "Es cierto... No hay duda de que es fiel al ramen de Kyushu No. 1 Star."

msgctxt "140_Annoyed Man"
msgid "I don't see any reason why I can't open my own Kyushu No. 1 Star shop. This ramen couldn't possibly disgrace the name!"
msgstr "No veo ninguna razón por la que no pueda abrir mi propio local de Kyushu No. 1 Star.\n"\n"¡Este ramen no podría deshonrar el nombre!"

msgctxt "152_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "Yes, the ramen you have here is very well-made."
msgstr "Sí, el ramen que tienes aquí está muy bien hecho."

msgctxt "164_Annoyed Man"
msgid "Okay, then why won't you let me open a new location!?"
msgstr "¡Entonces dime por qué no me dejas abrir un nuevo local!!!?"

msgctxt "176_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "Because no means no. Now, get back to work."
msgstr "Porque no es no. Ahora, vuelve al trabajo."

msgctxt "188_Man in Suit"
msgid "Ouch..."
msgstr "Ouch..."

msgctxt "200_Annoyed Man"
msgid "I know what it is! You just don't want me to go out on my own!"
msgstr "¡Ya sé lo que pasa! ¡Simplemente no quieres que me independice!"

msgctxt "224_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "236_Kiryu"
msgid "Hey, I'll have a bowl."
msgstr "Ey, me serviré un tazón."

msgctxt "248_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "Ah, if it isn't Kiryu-san!"
msgstr "¡Ah, si es Kiryu-san!"

msgctxt "260_Ueda"
msgid "Oh, Kiryu-san! Remember me? Ueda, from Acecook. Nice to see you again!"
msgstr "¡Oh, Kiryu-san! ¿Me recuerdas? Ueda, de Acecook.\n"\n"¡Qué bueno verte de nuevo!"

msgctxt "272_Kiryu"
msgid "Oh, right. You were the one who made an instant version of the ramen here. It's been a while. You still come here?"
msgstr "Ah, cierto. Tú fuiste quien hizo la versión instantánea del ramen de aquí. Ha pasado un tiempo. ¿Sigues viniendo?"

msgctxt "284_Ueda"
msgid "Of course! I'm a huge fan of this place."
msgstr "¡Por supuesto! Soy un gran fanático de este lugar."

msgctxt "296_Kiryu"
msgid "Heh. Right, I remember."
msgstr "Je. Sí, lo recuerdo."

msgctxt "308_Kiryu"
msgid "By the way, who was that just now? Your apprentice?"
msgstr "Por cierto, ¿quién era ese de antes? ¿Tu aprendiz?"

msgctxt "320_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "That's right. His name's Matsuyama. He's young, but he's got plenty of determination and skill."
msgstr "Así es. Se llama Matsuyama. Es joven, pero tiene mucha determinación y habilidad."

msgctxt "332_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "He's really mastered our ramen. I can't wait to see what he'll do in the future."
msgstr "Ha dominado nuestro ramen. No puedo esperar a ver qué hará en el futuro."

msgctxt "344_Kiryu"
msgid "But you don't want him to open his own shop?"
msgstr "Pero no quieres que abra su propio local, ¿verdad?"

msgctxt "356_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "Well, that's..."
msgstr "Bueno, eso es..."

msgctxt "368_Ueda"
msgid "I'm sure it's not that you don't want to expand... I'm guessing you have your own reasons?"
msgstr "Estoy seguro de que no es que no quieras expandirte... ¿Me imagino que tienes tus razones.?"

msgctxt "380_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "......"
msgstr "......"

msgctxt "392_Ueda"
msgid "Would you like to talk about it? I'd like to help, if I could."
msgstr "¿Te gustaría hablar sobre ello? Me gustaría ayudar si puedo."

msgctxt "404_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "I hate to burden customers with our problems... but I suppose I can tell you."
msgstr "Odio cargar a los clientes con nuestros problemas... pero supongo que puedo contártelo."

msgctxt "416_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "Matsuyama's plenty good, that's for sure. But do you really think there's any point in him just making the same ramen as I do?"
msgstr "Matsuyama es muy bueno, eso es seguro, pero ¿de verdad crees que tiene sentido que solo haga el mismo ramen que yo?"

msgctxt "428_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "With the skill and intensity he's got, I'd like to see him make something only he's capable of."
msgstr "Con la habilidad e intensidad que tiene, me gustaría verlo crear algo que solo él sea capaz de hacer."

msgctxt "440_Kiryu"
msgid "So you think he ought to go into business on his own, rather than just opening a new branch of Kyushu No. 1 Star."
msgstr "Así que crees que debería emprender por su cuenta en lugar de simplemente abrir\n"\n"una nueva sucursal del Kyushu No. 1 Star."

msgctxt "452_Ueda"
msgid "That's how you really feel?"
msgstr "¿Eso es lo que realmente sientes?"

msgctxt "464_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "That's right..."
msgstr "That's right..."

msgctxt "476_Ueda"
msgid "And you couldn't just say that to Matsuyama-san?\\r\n"\n"Actually, knowing you, I guess that's not likely."
msgstr "¿Y no podrías simplemente decirle eso a Matsuyama-san? Aunque, conociéndote, supongo que eso no es muy probable."

msgctxt "488_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "You nuts!? What good's it gonna do for me to tell him? He's gotta see it for himself."
msgstr "¿Estás loco!? ¿De qué serviría que yo se lo dijera? Tiene que darse cuenta por sí mismo."

msgctxt "500_Ueda"
msgid "It seems like he's really serious, though..."
msgstr "Aunque parece que realmente se lo está tomando en serio..."

msgctxt "512_Owner of Kyushu No. 1 Star"
msgid "Anyway, enough of this talk. Sorry to bother you with our troubles. Enjoy your ramen!"
msgstr "En fin, basta de esto. Perdón por molestarlos con nuestros problemas. ¡Disfruten su ramen!"

msgctxt "524_Kiryu"
msgid "Thanks."
msgstr "Gracias."

msgctxt "536_Ueda"
msgid "Matsuyama-san really seemed to have his heart set on opening a new branch."
msgstr "Matsuyama-san realmente parecía decidido a abrir una nueva sucursal."

msgctxt "548_Kiryu"
msgid "Yeah, he seemed pretty upset about it."
msgstr "Sí, parecía bastante molesto por eso."

msgctxt "560_Ueda"
msgid "Kiryu-san, I know it's none of my business, but do you think it would be okay to let Matsuyama-san know how the owner really feels about this whole thing?"
msgstr "Kiryu-san, sé que no es asunto mío, pero...\n"\n"¿crees que estaría bien hacerle saber a Matsuyama-san lo que realmente siente el dueño sobre todo esto?"

msgctxt "572_Kiryu"
msgid "Remember what the owner said? There are some things you have to figure out on your own."
msgstr "¿Recuerdas lo que dijo el dueño? Hay cosas que uno tiene que descubrir por sí mismo."

msgctxt "584_Ueda"
msgid "I can see where he's coming from and all, but..."
msgstr "Sí, entiendo su punto de vista, pero..."

msgctxt "596_Kiryu"
msgid "Yeah, it seems he will never know otherwise. I'll see what I can do to help."
msgstr "Sí, parece que, si nadie le dice nada, nunca lo sabrá. Veré qué puedo hacer para ayudar."

msgctxt "608_Ueda"
msgid "You will!? Thanks! Let's go find Matsuyama-san!"
msgstr "¿De verdad!? ¡Gracias!\n"\n"¡Busquemos a Matsuyama-san!"

msgctxt "620_Kiryu"
msgid "Any idea where he might be?"
msgstr "¿Tienes idea de dónde podría estar?"

msgctxt "632_Ueda"
msgid "Uh, well..."
msgstr "Eh, bueno..."

msgctxt "644_Kiryu"
msgid "No? Oh, well. It's not like he could've gone far. Let's split up and look for him."
msgstr "Oh, bueno. No es como si pudiera haber ido muy lejos.\n"\n"Dividámonos y busquémoslo."

msgctxt "656_Ueda"
msgid "Sounds good. I'll call you if I find him!"
msgstr "¡Me parece bien! Te llamaré si lo encuentro.!"

msgctxt "668_Kiryu"
msgid "Sure. I'll do the same."
msgstr "Seguro. Yo haré lo mismo."

msgctxt "680_Kiryu"
msgid "(He just ran off with his uniform still on, so he should be easy to spot. I should try asking if anybody saw him.)"
msgstr "(Todavía lleva puesto su uniforme, así que debería ser fácil de reconocer.\n"\n"Debería preguntar si alguien lo vio.)"

msgctxt "704_Annoyed Man"
msgid "I could help with that."
msgstr "Podría ayudar con eso."

msgctxt "716_Annoyed Man"
msgid "Just leave him be."
msgstr "Solo déjalo ser."

